      • msgfunc

        public void msgfunc(lpsolve.LpSolve solver,
           java.lang.Object handle,
           int message)
             throws lpsolve.LpSolveException
        Description copied from interface: lpsolve.MsgListener
        This routine is called when a situation specified in the mask parameter of putMsgfunc occurs. Note that this routine is called while solving the model. This can be usefull to follow the solving progress.
        Specified by:
        msgfunc in interface lpsolve.MsgListener
        Parameters:
        solver - the problem this Listener was defined for
        handle - the userhandle object that was passed to putMsgfunc
        message - event code why this method was called
        Throws:
        lpsolve.LpSolveException
